  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "Credibility assessment for CFD-based prediction of absolute hemolysis index in the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump operating under ventricular assist device conditions. The model is a steady-state, incompressible Navier-Stokes solver coupled with a power-law hemolysis damage accumulation model. The intended use scope — prediction of normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) for a Class III VAD at 5 L/min and 3500 RPM operating point to support a 510(k) substantial-equivalence submission — is described fully in the Claim and Requirement nodes bound below. Model Risk Level is 5 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 1, driven by high consequence of model error and absence of direct patient-specific validation data. Thirteen credibility factors were evaluated; seven achieved assessed status with achieved levels uniformly below required levels; six were flagged not-assessed due to epistemic gaps at MRL 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification (n=2000 LHS samples) was completed. Despite prose richness of the requirement and claim records, no structured hasContextOfUse node is linked from this UnitOfAssurance — the intended-use scope is implicit in the bound artefacts only, constituting the W-ON-01 ontological gap.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/vad-hemolysis-cou2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cfd-hemolysis-vad-mrl5",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-v3",
