    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-review-board",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted this UnitOfAssurance under the Minimal profile on the basis that the bound Requirement (https://uofa.net/morrison/req/vad-hemolysis-cou2) and Claim (https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cfd-hemolysis-vad-mrl5) nodes jointly articulate the intended-use scope for the Class III VAD hemolysis prediction. The team judged that the prose descriptions within those artefacts — specifying the 5 L/min, 3500 RPM operating envelope and the 510(k) submission context — were sufficient to establish scope without a separately linked hasContextOfUse object. This judgment is the structural gap targeted by W-ON-01: the absence of a machine-readable hasContextOfUse link means automated systems cannot resolve the intended-use boundary, and downstream scope-drift checks cannot be executed against a structured COU node.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
